c: 4
v: 141
t: "who but wait to see what betides you: thus, if triumph comes to you from God, they say, \"Were we not on your side?\"- whereas if those who deny the truth are in luck, they say [to them], \"Have we not earned your affection by defending you against those believers?'' But God will judge between you all on the Day of Resurrection; and never will God allow those who deny the truth to harm the believers"